# Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP)

## What is HTTP?

HTTP is the protocol used by web browsers and web servers to communicate.

## HTTP Request Methods

### GET
Retrieves data from a server.

### POST
Sends data to a server.

### PUT
Updates existing data.

### DELETE
Removes data.

## Common Status Codes

### 200 OK
Request was successful.

### 301 Moved Permanently
Resource has moved.

### 404 Not Found
Requested page does not exist.

### 500 Internal Server Error
Problem occurred on the server.

## HTTPS

HTTPS is the secure version of HTTP and uses TLS encryption to protect data during transmission.

## Key Learning

HTTP enables communication between browsers and web servers, while HTTPS adds confidentiality and security. 
